Business realities are changing for big technology suppliers as corporate customers depend less on products and more on services.











                    Up and Out of New York’s Projects                
Some of Sonia Sotomayor’s fellow alumni of New York’s housing projects recall growing up in the 1940s, ’50s and ’60s in a fairly safe place where doors stayed unlocked.











                    Private Sector; An Apparent Heir at Xerox                
URSULA M. BURNS doesn't play golf. She doesn't belong to the local country club. Small talk is not her strong suit. And she insists on being home on weekends. She sounds like an unlikely climber on the Xerox corporate ladder. But up she is going, rung by rung. Since she joined the company two decades ago, Ms. Burns has moved through engineering, manufacturing, various product divisions and a senior vice presidency.













